Roles & Responsibilities
About the Company
Our Client is a global leader in transportation and supply management.
Responsibilities
We’re looking for an experienced team player in the role of HR Executive, Payroll to perform the full spectrum of payroll activities for a 6-month maternity cover.
Perform end-to-end processing of payroll for employees;
Address any queries on payroll matters;
Maintain the HR systems and oversee leave applications, claims and other benefits;
Support with submissions for CPF, tax and other statutory payments, which may include coordination with vendors;
Oversee employee welfare benefits with the appropriate vendors;
Administer submissions for work pass matters;
Provide HR support for matters such as termination, resignations or relocations;
Support internal and external audits;
Stay updated on regulations and statutory rules;
Perform monthly or ad-hoc reports to various departments.
Requirements
Tertiary education in any discipline;
At least 3 years of relevant work experience in payroll in a similar capacity;
Strong understanding of payroll and statutory contributions;
Proficiency in HR systems and Microsoft Excel;
Good communication skill, both written and verbal;
Good interpersonal skills and ability to work well in a team;
Ability to work under pressure and tight timeframes.
Employment Details
Contract Period: November 2023 – May 2024 or December 2023 – June 2024;
Work location is in the East;
Flexible work arrangement (50% remote working).
Get in touch with us
If you’d like to explore this opportunity, please reach out to Charmaine Tan (Regn No. R1102130) at charmaine@fcs-careers.com for a confidential discussion.

FCS CAREERS PTE LTD (EA 94C4359)

